{
  "name": "Glowing Coin",
  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>When you cast the spell, you hurl the coin that is the spell's material component to any spot within range. The coin lights up as if under the effect of a @spell[light] spell. Each creature of your choice that you can see within 30 feet of the coin must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be distracted for the duration. While distracted, a creature has disadvantage on Wisdom (@skill[Perception]) checks and initiative rolls.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"><p></p></div></div>",
